[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = EHTNCDBase","category":"page"},{"location":"#EHTNCDBase","page":"Home","title":"EHTNCDBase","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for EHTNCDBase.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [EHTNCDBase]","category":"page"},{"location":"#EHTNCDBase.ncdmodes","page":"Home","title":"EHTNCDBase.ncdmodes","text":"ncdmodes::NamedTuple\n\nA named tuple relating Symbols to actual strings for the access mode to netCDF files using NCDatasets.jl. Keys are:\n\nKeys and Values\n\n:read:    open an existing netCDF file or OPeNDAP URL in read-only mode (\"r\" in NCDatasets.jl).\n:create:   create a new NetCDF file (an existing file with the same name will be overwritten;   \"c\" in NCDatasets.jl)\n:append:   open filename into append mode (i.e. existing data in the netCDF file is    not overwritten; \"a\" in NCDatasets.jl)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#EHTNCDBase.define_group-Tuple{NCDatasets.NCDataset, AbstractVector}","page":"Home","title":"EHTNCDBase.define_group","text":"define_group(dataset, groups) -> NCDataset\n\nDefine the given group in the given dataset.\n\nArguments\n\ndataset::NCDataset:   Input dataset\ngroups::AbstractVector:   A vector of strings for the path of the group.   Assuming that this is an output of split_group.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EHTNCDBase.get_group-Tuple{NCDatasets.NCDataset, AbstractVector}","page":"Home","title":"EHTNCDBase.get_group","text":"get_group(dataset, groups) -> NCDataset\n\nGet the given group specified in the given NCDataset.\n\nArguments\n\ndataset::NCDataset:   Input dataset\ngroups::AbstractVector:   A vector of strings for the path of the group.   Assuming that this is an output of split_group.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EHTNCDBase.split_group-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"Home","title":"EHTNCDBase.split_group","text":"split_group(group) -> Vector{String}\n\nPurse the input path of the group and split it into a vector.\n\nArguments\n\ngroup::AbstractString: Input path of the group\n\nExamples\n\njulia> split_group(\"rootgroup/subgroup/subsubgroup\")\n3-element Vector{String}:\n \"rootgroup\"\n \"subgroup\"\n \"subsubgroup\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
